YOLA – History was made on Friday as Aishatu Binani, a senator representing Adamawa Central senatorial district, has emerged as the winner of the All Progressives Congress (APC) governorship primary election in Adamawa State. This was made known as the Chairman of the APC Adamawa State Electoral Committee, Gambo Lawal, announced the result on Friday. Senator Binanidefeated beat five other contenders, all men, to clinch the ticket. Mrs. Binani scored 430 votes to defeat her closest rival and a former Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), Nuhu Ribadu, who got 288 votes. The former governor, Bindow Jibrilla had 103 votes to clinch the third position. The election, which started at about 11:30 pm on Thursday, was concluded at about 8:44 on Friday morning. This victory makes Binani the first woman to win the governorship ticket of a major party in the state. . By IBRAHIM KADO Governor Ahmadu Fintiri YOLA- No fewer than 663 delegates on Wednesday elected Gov. Ahmadu Fintiri of Adamawa as the People’s Democratic Party’s (PDP) governorship candidate to contest the 2023 election for a second term of office.Dr Gibon Katabs, Chairman of the electoral committee of the primary election… In "Politics" Abuja - No fewer than 30 senators may not make it back to the parliament in 2023 when the 10th National Assembly would be inaugurated.  While some are pursuing other aspirations, paving the way for other aspirants to take over their seats in the Red Chamber, the re-election bids of… In "Top Stories" "If we (PDP) go in a hurry and nominate someone from Zone C (Benue South), and our opponent (APC) does not do same in Tiv land, it means that the PDP will lose the (governorship) election completely, even with the overwhelming support that we have today in PDP. That is… In "Politics"